


git instructions 

list git configurations 
	git config --list

create git repository

	git init

add files 

	git add -a

check if everything has been committed 

	git status

	git commit 

check abbreviated stats for each commit

	git log --stat

	specify date : git log --since=2.weeks --stat

REMOTE REPOSITORIES 

add

	git remote add <shortname> <url>:

	for ssh ssh://ubuntu@IpADDRESS/var/repo/REPONAME.git (here uses repo, not html folder!!)

see info 

	git remote show <shortname>

retrieve data from a remote repository
	
	git fetch <shortname>

	git pull <shortname> -> fetches data and merge into local repository

pushing 

	git push <remote> <branch>

Renaming and Removing 

	git remote rename <old name> <new name>

	git remote remove <name>


BRANCHES

see all branches 

	git branch

see last commit for each branch 

	git branch -v

create 

	git branch <branch name>

switch to branch 

	git checkout <branch name>


create and switch to 

	git checkout -b <branch name>

delete 

	git branch -d <branch name>

merging 

	git checkout master ( imagining you want to merge branch into master, but master can also be merged into branches!)
	git merge <branch name>

see where project has divergent history (last 2 weeks)

 git log --since=2.weeks --oneline --decorate --graph --all




